en: Temporal Dominance of Sensation (TDS) makes possible to collect temporal data during one single evaluation for several attributes. The method consists in presenting the entire set of attributes to the panellist on the computer screen. Along the tasting of one product, the panellist has to wonder what the dominant sensory perception is and to select and score the corresponding attribute. Each time the panellist thinks the dominant sensory perception has changed, either in intensity or in quality, he has to score the new perception.
